-- Bahrain Islamic bank Al Baraka posts near-flat Q1 profit
-- By David French
-- Sun May 11, 2014 07:35AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, May 11 (Reuters) - Bahrain-based Al Baraka Banking Group <BARKA.BH> reported near-flat first-quarter net profit on Sunday.

The Islamic lender recorded a net attributable profit of $36.6 million in the three months to March 31, compared with $36.8 million in the corresponding period of 2013, the bank said in a bourse filing.